fields.about:
So you want to hear about meàwellà
I have always liked computers and have had too many to mention since the first ZX81 which my parents bought, for 3 young boys, a very long time ago.  ItÆs probably still around somewhere.  I spent hours with my brothers, trying to program it using magazine articles that weÆd acquired by post; getting round its precarious quirks and temperamentality.  I canÆt say that I feel especially nostalgic about it, apart from the bit about my brothers.  Needless to say, the following decades of my life have been punctuated by countless developments in technology and gaming as well as my involvement in computing and the associated community.
Over the past 25 years I have worked on a whole range of projects in oil and gas, banking and finance and with third sector and public sector organizations, not to mention individuals. 
Setting up my own website and freelancing has evolved more by chance than design.  As people locally, nationally and internationally tried to navigate their lives and livelihoods following that day in March 2020 when it became apparent that the Covid pandemic was going to change the world quite drastically; I was approached by several people and groups to help.  Working from home gave me the time and flexibility to do this and all took off from there. 
When IÆm not working with computers and projects for clients, I spend a fair bit of time renovating our family home; a former youth hostel.  Like many such undertakings, itÆs a labour of love and gets picked up and put down as life dictates.  I also spend a lot of time with my children and in the early days was ôitö while my wife went back to work.  I have no problem getting round the supermarket with a 4 year old, 2 year old and an 8 week old baby and getting home in time to rustle up lunch.  Nowadays the demands and requirements of teenagers are quite different but the family is still very much part of my life.    
I also like to find time to exercise and was quite a fan of Arnold Schwarzenegger back in the day.
I hope that you enjoy my site and find what you are looking for.  If what you need doesnÆt immediately jump out, get in touch anyway as the chances are I can help.  I look forward to hearing from you.
